Defendant Eric Cortez Gilmore in court with attorney Daniel E Meylink.  Defendant Eric Cortez Gilmore in custody.  Megan Patricia Carmody appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY to the amended charge and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Amended Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by State, Defense and Defendant.  Additional statement by:  Rosamaria V.

The Court sentenced defendant to serve 8 MONTHS in the House of Corrections, consecutive to COUNT 2 and any other sentence,  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions:
-Restitution in the amount of $2,222.48 payable to Rosamaria V. payable by applying cash bail on deposit, remaining balance to be paid during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
